sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Walt Disney Co. (Symbol: DIS), where a total of 40,510 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 4.1 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 47.1% of DIS's average daily trading volume over the past month of 8.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $96 strike put option expiring June 10, 2016 , with 8,003 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 800,300 underlying shares of DIS.

JPMorgan Chase & Co (Symbol: JPM) options are showing a volume of 61,507 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 6.2 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 46.5% of JPM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 13.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $63.50 strike call option expiring June 10, 2016 , with 4,207 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 420,700 underlying shares of JPM.

Below is a chart showing JPM's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $63.50 strike highlighted in orange:

And Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD) options are showing a volume of 22,656 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 2.3 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 46.1% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.9 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $133 strike call option expiring May 20, 2016 , with 1,578 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 157,800 underlying shares of HD.
